<Link id="l00762" /><CodeLine lineNumber="762"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Below is the pattern that is used to figure out the archive format</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00763" /><CodeLine lineNumber="763"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// GNU archive format</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00764" /><CodeLine lineNumber="764"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  First member : / (may exist, if it exists, points to the symbol table )</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00765" /><CodeLine lineNumber="765"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Second member : // (may exist, if it exists, points to the string table)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00766" /><CodeLine lineNumber="766"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Note : The string table is used if the filename exceeds 15 characters</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00767" /><CodeLine lineNumber="767"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// BSD archive format</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00768" /><CodeLine lineNumber="768"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  First member : &#95;&#95;.SYMDEF or &quot;&#95;&#95;.SYMDEF SORTED&quot; (the symbol table)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00769" /><CodeLine lineNumber="769"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  There is no string table, if the filename exceeds 15 characters or has a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00770" /><CodeLine lineNumber="770"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  embedded space, the filename has #1/&lt;size&gt;, The size represents the size</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00771" /><CodeLine lineNumber="771"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  of the filename that needs to be read after the archive header</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00772" /><CodeLine lineNumber="772"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// COFF archive format</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00773" /><CodeLine lineNumber="773"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  First member : /</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00774" /><CodeLine lineNumber="774"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Second member : / (provides a directory of symbols)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00775" /><CodeLine lineNumber="775"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Third member : // (may exist, if it exists, contains the string table)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00776" /><CodeLine lineNumber="776"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  Note: Microsoft PE/COFF Spec 8.3 says that the third member is present</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00777" /><CodeLine lineNumber="777"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  even if the string table is empty. However, lib.exe does not in fact</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00778" /><CodeLine lineNumber="778"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  seem to create the third member if there&#39;s no member whose filename</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00779" /><CodeLine lineNumber="779"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//  exceeds 15 characters. So the third member is optional.</span></CodeLine>
